<BLOCK1><TI>AFFIDAVIT</TI>
<P>I, Philip van Wassenaer, of the City of Mississauga, in the Province of Ontario, MAKE OATH AND SAY:</P>
<P>1. I am arborist retained by the respondents in this matter and, as such, have knowledge of the matters contained in this affidavit.</P>
<P>2. I have over 28 years of experience in the areas of arboriculture and urban forestry. I hold a Master's degree in Urban Forest Conservation (MFC) and Bachelor's degree in Environmental Science (B. Sc.). I am an International Society of Arboriculture (ISA) Certified Arborist, a member of the American Society of Consulting Arborists, a member of the Sachverst&au;ndigen-Arbeitsgemeinschaft Baumstatik (SAG), an association of European tree risk experts, and I am ISA Tree Risk Assessment Qualified.</P>
<P>3. I have been retained by counsel for Megan MacDougall and Nigel Scott to give opinion evidence pertaining to a dispute between them and the applicants, Drew Allen and Susan Byrne. In particular, I have been asked to comment on the nature and benefit of the tree that is the subject of this dispute, as well as the applicants' ability to develop their property while preserving that tree. A true copy of my executed Acknowledgement of Expert's Duty is attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;A&rdquo;</BOLD>.</P>
<P>4. My opinion is set out in the report dated January 8, 2019 (the &ldquo;<BOLD>van Wassenaer Report</BOLD>&rdquo;), attached as <BOLD>Exhibit &ldquo;B&rdquo;</BOLD> and which I adopt as my evidence. My qualifications are set out in the curriculum vitae attached as Appendix 6 to the van Wassenaer Report.</P>
<P>5. In preparing the van Wasssenaer Report, I reviewed the following documents:
<P1>(a) The Application Record of Drew Allen and Susan Byrne, including the Affidavit of Drew Allen sworn August 30, 2018 and its exhibits.</P1>
<P1>(b) The Affidavit of Meghan McDougall sworn January 8, 2019 and its exhibits.</P1></P>
<P>6. For the purposes of the van Wassenaer Report, I made the following assumptions:
<P1>(a) The documents cited above at paragraph 5 (i) are authentic, (ii) came into existence on or about the dates shown on their face, (iii) were created by the persons purporting to be the author and (iv) that such persons had the authority to create them;</P1>
<P1>(b) Any other assumptions I have made are set out in the van Wassenaer Report.</P1></P>
